            <additions>
              <list>
                <item xml:id="addition1" n="1">
                  <label>Colophon</label>
                  <locus from="114b"/>
                  <p>A note on fol. 114 b shows that the name of the scribe was <persName>John</persName>
                  </p>
                  <p>
                    <quote xml:lang="syr">ܟܠ ܡ̇ܢ ܕܩ̇ܪܐ ܒܟܬܒܐ ܗܢܐ ܢܨܠܐ ܥܠ ܝܘܚܢܢ ܚܛܝܐ ܕܟ̣ܬܒ ܕܢܬ̣ܚܢܢ ܒܝܘܡ ܕܝܢ̣ܐ ܐܝܟ ܓܝ̇ܣܐ
                      ܒܙܩܝܦܐ. ܒܨܠܘܬܗ ܕܟܠ ܕܫܦ̣ܪ ܘܫܦܪ ܠܡܪܢ܀</quote>
                  </p>
                </item>
                <item xml:id="addition2" n="2">
                  <locus from="114b"/>
                  <p>Below <ref>the note containging the name of the scribe</ref>, a reader named <persName ref="smblPers736">Daniel</persName> has written</p>
                  <p>
                    <quote xml:lang="syr">ܟܠܡ̇ܢ ܕܩ̇ܪܐ ܒܟܬܒܐ ܗܢܐ. ܢܨܠܐ ܥܠ ܕܢܝܐܠ ܚܛܝܐ ܕܢܬܚܢܢ ܒܝܘܡ
                      ܕܝܢ̣ܐ</quote>
                  </p>
                </item>
                <item xml:id="addition3" n="3">
                  <locus from="114b"/>
                  <p>Still lower down, we read in Karshūnῑ the name of one <persName ref="smblPers737">George, son of <persName ref="smblPers738">the priest Joseph</persName>
                    </persName>:</p>
                  <p>
